One interesting Note:  Tom mentioned that he was a twenty three year old combatant.  I believe that Tom has been hurt badly by experience and circumstance but has faired reasonably well.  Why?  Did he get more or less exposure to trauma than the next guy?  Does he simply cope better than others?<br>
Erickson theorizes about a fifth stage of development called intimacy Vs. isolation.  It is a very important stage in human development... sort of a pre cursor to maturity... certainly a criteria for making meaningful contracts and honoring them in the future... and above all developing interpersonal relationship skills.  Normally it occurs between the ages of 17 and 23 years.  Tom was a little more mature than the masses in RVN whose average age was 19 years and 3 months.<br>
Well, what about guys like Cookie (who I am assuming was pretty young)?  Remember, chronological age does not always agree with emotional age or level of maturation.  If that does not exempt Cook then some other factor must be considered.. i.e. spiritual strength, early indoctrination from significant males (father..uncles...Grandfather etc.), cultural values and so forth.<br><br>
To SW:  I agree!  Spatz doesn't know shit from Shineola.  The only way to deal with this &quot;party crasher&quot; is to ignore him.  He needs to understand rejection on a personal level... the unwarranted kind.  The problem is... he deserves to be rejected because of his lack of character, values and his sensational, attention seeking behavior.  He cannot erase the fact that he is a cowardly parasite anymore than I can erase the killing of children.<br>
God cannot forgive us for the things we did not do!  When I accept the fact that &quot;I&quot; killed children, instead of the U.S. Navy, U.S. Army.. Congress...LBJ..etc, then I can approach God with something &quot;I&quot; did wrong and get forgiveness (providing..I can forgive myself.)<br><br>
The acceptance I receive from my worthwhile brothers is a healing balm for my heart.  The crap I hear from Spatz is a thorn in my ass... which is my fault because I choose to react to his stupid comments.<br><br>
I feel a deep sadness for any vet who came across Spatz seeking counsel for PTSD, secondary to combat.  I think of a child molester running a day care center.<br><br>
